    "what are the symptoms of menopause?": "symptoms of menopause may include irregular periods, hot flashes, night sweats, vaginal dryness or discomfort during sex, sleep disturbances, mood changes, weight gain, slowed metabolism, thinning hair or hair loss, and dry skin. if you're experiencing symptoms of menopause that interfere with your quality of life, it's essential to seek medical evaluation and support.",
    "how can i manage menopause symptoms?": "to manage menopause symptoms, treatment options may include hormone replacement therapy (such as estrogen therapy or combined estrogen-progestin therapy), nonhormonal medications (such as selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors or gabapentin), lifestyle modifications (such as regular exercise, healthy diet, and stress management), and complementary therapies (such as acupuncture or herbal supplements). it's essential to work with a healthcare provider to develop an individualized treatment plan based on your specific symptoms, medical history, and preferences.",
    "what are the symptoms of polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS)?": "symptoms of polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) may vary, but common symptoms may include irregular periods or no periods, heavy periods, excess hair growth (hirsutism), acne, weight gain or difficulty losing weight, thinning hair on the scalp, darkening of the skin (acanthosis nigricans), skin tags, and difficulty getting pregnant. if you're experiencing symptoms of PCOS, it's essential to seek medical evaluation and treatment.",
